n\": 199, \"end\": 206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.014600121473328e-16, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 225, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902116856423117, \"rank\": 0.009885045831758537, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"February\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 218}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Games\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 287}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Individual Neutral Athletes\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, there are only 15 Russian athletes competing at the Summer Games in France this year.\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 374, \"end\": 381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902116856423117, \"rank\": 0.009885045831758537, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5685907883350607, \"rank\": 0.36006632275771816, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Summer Games\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Various Russian media outlets, the vast majority of which are linked to the Russian state, have appeared to revel in misfortunes and controversies - both significant and less so - that have sprung up during the competition, ranging from complaints over the catering in the Olympic Village to the gender furor in the women's boxing event.\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 451, \"end\": 458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902116856423117, \"rank\": 0.009885045831758537, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 519, \"end\": 526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902116856423117, \"rank\": 0.009885045831758537, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.447242865374225e-24, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the vast majority\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 491}, {\"ngram\": \"misfortunes\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 571}, {\"ngram\": \"controversies\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 589}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 650, \"to\": 665}, {\"ngram\": \"complaints\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 690}, {\"ngram\": \"the catering\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"the gender furor\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's boxing event\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With nothing to win and less to lose, Russia's media coverage of the Olympics has been invariably negative about the competition, host France and the organizer, the International Olympic Committee (IOC).\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.175903347036643e-19, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 917, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5685907883350607, \"rank\": 0.36006632275771816, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 947, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 859}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 910}, {\"ngram\": \"the organizer\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tone of the Russian media coverage was set straight after the opening ceremony, withthe Russian press honing in onthe \\\"scandal\\\" and \\\"disgrace\\\"caused by a segment of the pageant featuring drag queens, which was accused of mocking Christianity.\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1003, \"end\": 1010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902116856423117, \"rank\": 0.009885045831758537, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1220, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999199271802, \"rank\": 8.007292142093736e-08, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tone\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 995}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1069}, {\"ngram\": \"onthe \\\"scandal\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"a segment\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1152}, {\"ngram\": \"the pageant\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Claims by organizers that the segment was meant to represent a pagan feast were ridiculed by the Russian media, with weekly newspaper outlet Argumenty i Fakty describing it asthe \\\"Olympus of Hell\\\"and reporting that \\\"the world\\\" had condemned the \\\"blasphemous\\\" opening event.\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1298, \"end\": 1303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"score\": 0.9999999756064429, \"rank\": 2.4376235166778512e-08, \"text\": \"pagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\"}, {\"begin\": 1332, \"end\": 1339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902116856423117, \"rank\": 0.009885045831758537, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Claims\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1241}, {\"ngram\": \"organizers\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1255}, {\"ngram\": \"the segment\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1272}, {\"ngram\": \"weekly newspaper outlet Argumenty\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"i Fakty\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1393}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Olympus\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1422}, {\"ngram\": \"Hell\\\"and\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1434}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"blasphemous\\\" opening event\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1507}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Russian media has subsequently portrayed the Games as misrun and mismanaged, focusing on crime, controversy and pollution at the event, and accusing host France of havinga cavalier and careless approach to the well-being of athletes.\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1514, \"end\": 1521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902116856423117, \"rank\": 0.009885045831758537, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1668, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5685907883350607, \"rank\": 0.36006632275771816, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavalier\", \"score\": 0.9999975197682778, \"rank\": 2.480237698217021e-06, \"text\": \"cavalier\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavalier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavalier\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1564}, {\"ngram\": \"misrun\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"crime\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1621}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1635}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1648}, {\"ngram\": \"host\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1667}, {\"ngram\": \"the well-being\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1746}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A British athlete complaining about worms found in fish served to athletes in the Olympic Villagewas reported with relish Tuesday, while a Covid-19 outbreak affecting more than 40 athletes,according to the World Health Organization, is a popular talking point.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999996338829749, \"rank\": 1.6084048158618365e-07, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1955, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Health_Organization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0159504713929188e-38, \"text\": \"World Health Organization\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Health_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Health_Organization\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"worms\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1790}, {\"ngram\": \"fish\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1804}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Villagewas\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"relish\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1870}, {\"ngram\": \"a Covid-19 outbreak\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 1905}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 40 athletes\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1937}, {\"ngram\": \"a popular talking point\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2008}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Likewise, with the quality of the water of the River Seine in Paris: Russian media outlets have had a field day with news of canceled training sessions and a postponed race due to bacterial readings.\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2058, \"end\": 2069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2073, \"end\": 2078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.491129617781147e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2080, \"end\": 2087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russ