\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.175903347036643e-19, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a possibility\", \"from\": 4077, \"to\": 4090}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4105}, {\"ngram\": \"previous tournaments\", \"from\": 4116, \"to\": 4136}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 4170, \"to\": 4179}, {\"ngram\": \"first time\", \"from\": 4187, \"to\": 4197}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Along with rampant anti-Western rhetoric by the Kremlin and state media, this has damped down Russian public interest in the competition.\", \"from\": 4228, \"to\": 4365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4276, \"end\": 4283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999432411658, \"rank\": 5.6758936032478206e-08, \"text\": \"Kremlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4322, \"end\": 4329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902116856423117, \"rank\": 0.009885045831758537, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rampant anti-Western rhetoric\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4268}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4364}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Russia was already smarting fromthe World Anti-Doping Agency's decision in 2019 to ban the country from international sports competitions for four years.\", \"from\": 4367, \"to\": 4520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4367, \"end\": 4373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.175903347036643e-19, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fromthe World Anti-Doping Agency's decision\", \"from\": 4395, \"to\": 4438}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 4454, \"to\": 4465}, {\"ngram\": \"international sports competitions\", \"from\": 4471, \"to\": 4504}, {\"ngram\": \"four years\", \"from\": 4509, \"to\": 4519}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That came after the country was found to be running a large-scale, state-sponsored doping scheme, which Moscow denied overseeing.\", \"from\": 4521, \"to\": 4650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4625, \"end\": 4631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2337477638157051e-26, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 4537, \"to\": 4548}, {\"ngram\": \"a large-scale, state-sponsored doping scheme\", \"from\": 4573, \"to\": 4617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ban meant that Russian athletes had to compete under the banner of the \\\"Russian Olympic Committee\\\" at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics - which took place in 2021 due to the Covid-19 pandemic - and at the 2022 Winter Olympics in Beijing, held just days before the invasion of Ukraine.\", \"from\": 4652, \"to\": 4930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4671, \"end\": 4678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9902116856423117, \"rank\": 0.009885045831758537, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4728, \"end\": 4753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999997016857, \"rank\": 2.968470726369963e-10, \"text\": \"Russian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": 